    • createBlog

      @PostMapping("") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Blog> createBlog(@Valid @RequestBody @Valid Blog blog) throws URISyntaxException
      POST /blogs : Create a new blog.
      Parameters:
      blog - the blog to create.
      Returns:
      the ResponseEntity with status 201 (Created) and with body the new blog, or with status 400 (Bad Request) if the blog has already an ID.
      Throws:
      URISyntaxException - if the Location URI syntax is incorrect.

    • updateBlog

      @PutMapping("/{id}") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Blog> updateBlog(@PathVariable(value="id",required=false) Long id, @Valid @RequestBody @Valid Blog blog) throws URISyntaxException
      PUT /blogs/:id : Updates an existing blog.
      Parameters:
      id - the id of the blog to save.
      blog - the blog to update.
      Returns:
      the ResponseEntity with status 200 (OK) and with body the updated blog, or with status 400 (Bad Request) if the blog is not valid, or with status 500 (Internal Server Error) if the blog couldn't be updated.
      Throws:
      URISyntaxException - if the Location URI syntax is incorrect.

    • partialUpdateBlog

      @PatchMapping(value="/{id}", consumes={"application/json","application/merge-patch+json"}) public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Blog> partialUpdateBlog(@PathVariable(value="id",required=false) Long id, @NotNull @RequestBody @NotNull Blog blog) throws URISyntaxException
      PATCH /blogs/:id : Partial updates given fields of an existing blog, field will ignore if it is null
      Parameters:
      id - the id of the blog to save.
      blog - the blog to update.
      Returns:
      the ResponseEntity with status 200 (OK) and with body the updated blog, or with status 400 (Bad Request) if the blog is not valid, or with status 404 (Not Found) if the blog is not found, or with status 500 (Internal Server Error) if the blog couldn't be updated.
      Throws:
      URISyntaxException - if the Location URI syntax is incorrect.

    • getAllBlogs

      @GetMapping("") public List<Blog> getAllBlogs(@RequestParam(name="eagerload",required=false,defaultValue="true") boolean eagerload)
      GET /blogs : get all the blogs.
      Parameters:
